2. <App/> element full example:
        <App name="ABC Reading" packageName="com.tal.abctimelibrary">
            <StartUp>fullscreen</StartUp> // default value (when it's not present in <App/> element): undefined
            <Unsupported>toggleIcon</Unsupported> // default (when it's not present in <App/>): can maximize & restore
            <Unsupported>resize</Unsupported> // default (when it's not present in <App/>): can resize
            <Unsupported>move</Unsupported> // default (when it's not present in <App/>): can move
            <Unsupported>relunch</Unsupported> // when set, it don't relaunh because of SCREEN_LAYOUT.
            <Unsupported>fullrelaunch</Unsupported> // When set , it can't relaunch any time when pcmode.
            <Unsupported>kill</Unsupported> // When set, it can't be killed when close by X-icon or Nav-Bar-icon.
        </App>
See enumerations for every element in the corresponding Xml Schema Definition file,
pcmode_app_window_config_schema.xsd

3. Validate this file:
$ sudo apt install libxml2-utils
$ xmllint &#45;&#45;noout &#45;&#45;schema pcmode_app_window_config_schema.xsd pcmode_app_window_config.xml
(&#45; is ASCII 45, a hyphen `-`. Double hyphens are not allowed in XML comments.)
-->
<AppWindowConfig xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="./pcmode_app_window_config_schema.xsd"
    versionName="1.3.11" versionCode="18" date="20210517">
    <AppList>
        <App name="UC浏览器" packageName="com.UCMobile">
            <StartUp>fullscreen</StartUp>
            <Unsupported>toggleIcon</Unsupported>
            <Unsupported>resize</Unsupported>
            <Unsupported>relaunch</Unsupported>
        </App>
    </AppList>
</AppWindowConfig>
